Further engagement with officials on subject and request for two articles by Holyrood magazine</gtr:impact><gtr:outcomeId>546d0c91f11f80.40461293</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:partOfOfficialScheme>false</gtr:partOfOfficialScheme><gtr:primaryAudience>Policymakers/parliamentarians</gtr:primaryAudience><gtr:year>2014</gtr:year></gtr:disseminationOutput></gtr:disseminationOutputs><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs><gtr:impactSummaryOutput><gtr:description>INFORMING DEBATE VIA DIFFERENT MEDIA

Much of the work involved contributing to public debates through addressing meetings, broadcasting and other media work. Over the course of the referendum (and since), my work on the Scottish Question has been used by media in various form. 
I was interviewed by BBC STV and Al-Jazeera regularly throughout the period of the referendum including references in online work. I advised BBC on an initiative on 16/17 year olds that ran throughout the referendum. This involved a group of 16/17 year olds - referred to as generation 2014 (http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01gf7rb) who were invited to participate in many BBC programmes (in many different forms). I met with the group and advised the senior producer on issues. I also involved Dr Jan Eichhorn, a colleagues at Edinburgh University, in this endeavour.

The following are amongst the key media contributions over the period of the fellowship:
25 November 2013: Provided commentary for BBC's Our Friends in the North, on the referendum debate and how this relates to debates on public service provision in Scandinavian countries.
30 November 2013: Provided live commentary on the publication of Scottish Government's Independence White Paper.
24 March 2014: Contributed to a documentary on the life of Margo MacDonald.
12 April 2014: Judge in finals of schools debate broadcast on Scottish Television.
In addition, I was the lead academic commentator on Scottish Television's overnight coverage of the referendum results.

The two books produced during the fellowship (one co-edited and other a single authored monograph - the latter included by Andy McSmith of the 'Independent' as one of his 'books of the year') provided the basis of much public engagement work.

